  "text": "As we all know, President Donald Trump has a history of failing to follow the rule of law, which is what led him to become the first convicted felon to serve as US president. Andrew Harnik / Getty ImagesConsidering his criminal history, his most recent post is profoundly concerning for any American who enjoys living in a democracy. Michael M. SantiagoRecently, President Trump's official X account shared a post that has garnered over 150 million views, that reads: \"He who saves his Country does not violate any Law.\" @realDonaldTrump / Via x.comThe White House has since doubled down by reposting his statement on the official White House X account alongside Trump's official presidential portrait. @WhiteHouse / Via x.comPeople are obviously really worried about what this all means, so let's take a look at some of their reactions:As you can imagine, people were appalled when they stumbled upon the post. @CamdenHutchison / Via x.com\"Wants to be a dictator. If you don't see it it means you don't want to,\" former Trump White House Communications Director Anthony Scaramucci said. @Scaramucci / Via x.comAnother user agreed, comparing Trump's words to statements by historical dictators. @/krassenstein / Via x.com\"This is literally a quote attributed to Napoleon Bonaparte — right before he orchestrated a coup, seized absolute power, and crowned himself Emperor in defiance of democracy,\" this person continued. @EdKrassen / Via x.com\"well this should end the fascism debate!\" this user agreed. @alex_shephard / Via x.comAnother person compared Trump's logic to the actions of alleged UnitedHealthcare CEO shooter Luigi Mangione, which many people saw as justifiable. @walterrothbard / Via x.comAnother user pleaded with Republicans to be bipartisan and speak out against Trump's words: @/jaynordlinger / Via x.comAnd Trump's former vice president Mike Pence seemingly decided to speak up, reposting an essay he wrote in 2010 called \"The Presidency and the Constitution.\" @Mike_Pence / Via x.comHere's a brief excerpt: \"The president is not our teacher, our tutor, our guide or ruler. He does not command us; we command him. We serve neither him nor his vision.\"In conclusion, this person said what many people reading Trump's post are thinking: \"He's getting ready to do something really fucking illegal.\" @Angry_Staffer / Via x.comWhat are your thoughts? Let us know in the comments.",
